arChildNodes.szComment:
The PLAYER is looking out over the bridge at the dead BOATMAN, Hollow tendrils emerging from his corpse. Birds take flight from the river. 
The Player whips around to find URIVAR standing there with a squad of Knights.

Urivar wears a frightening horned mask. He peers at the Player, wordlessly tilting his head. 
He then slowly removes the mask and lights a cigar as he speaks.
The Player steps back, wary, hands ready to draw their weapon.
Urivar drops his cigar as more knights drag Raheir, burned and maimed, forward. Dropping him to the ground.
Knights drop Raheir to the ground.

Urivar places his sword at Raheir’s neck, but the Player’s had enough.
See QST_EX1_Knight_Cine_TBK_Alt for an alternate line: "You bastard!"

They draw their sword, ready to fight, but then...
We hear a chilling, haunting chant in a hoarse voice growing louder and louder. It’s hard to tell, but the voice is Neyrelle’s. 
We see an image of Neyrelle sitting in the boat, clutching the stone and chanting.

Time resumes pace as we hear the SHUNK of a blade sinking into flesh.
Urivar has stabbed the Player in the back.
He draws in close to whisper in their ear as they stumble.

This will be several Knights saying this single line in unison. The audio team will have to manually combine several takes into a group line.
After this, Urivar kicks the Player off the bridge. Beneath, the river rages over jagged rocks. 
The Player’s body misses the rocks and plunges into the water. 
They struggle at their clothing/gear surfacing once, then twice, but the current is too violent to overcome. 
They are pulled beneath the waves.

The player  floats face up in the river, blood seeping into the water around them. As they float, we see onscreen text: the prophecy. 

I saw my corpse, 
and from my mouth crawled Hatred, 
A father burned his children on a pyre, 
And a mother molded a new age from the ashes, 

I saw the weak made strong, 
a pack of lambs feasting on wolves, 
Tears of blood rained upon a desert jewel, 
and the way to Hell was torn asunder, 

Then came a spear of light, piercing Hatred’s heart, 
And he who was bound in chains was set free. 

The Player’s corpse lays on the ground now. ERU runs up and kneels beside them. He pushes down against the player’s chest, almost like a chest compression. Magic glows on his hands.

The Player comes to sudden consciousness with a wild-eyed gasp. 
THE PLAYER looks around, seeing the River Gate, then looking at ERU.
